  General methodology: The global approach considered in this     4759 1451
          work is presented in the following paper: Modern        4759 1451
          nuclear data evaluation with the TALYS code system,     4759 1451
          A.J. Koning and D. Rochman, Nuclear Data Sheets 113     4759 1451
          (2012) 2841.                                            4759 1451
                                                                  4759 1451
  MF2:  Resolved resonance range  (RRR)                           4759 1451
       The RRR was generated with TARES-1.31, compiled on         4759 1451
       12-10-2015 11:58:11 PM at Villingen  , Switzerland. The RRR4759 1451
       expands from 0 to 2.838099E+2 eV. A total of               4759 1451
       2 l-values are used and 16 resonances. The resonance       4759 1451
       formalism is multi-level Breit Wigner (MLBW).              4759 1451
       The ladder approach from the CALENDF code is used to       4759 1451
       generate statistical resonances in the unresolved          4759 1451
       resonance range. Therefore, the URR is translated into     4759 1451
       resolved resonance range. Explanations about the method    4759 1451
       can be found in the CALENDF manual: CEA-Report CEA-R-6277  4759 1451
       "CALENDF-2010: User manual" by J.C. Sublet, P. Ribon and   4759 1451
       M. Coste-Delcaux.                                          4759 1451
       The method of creating statistical resonances in the       4759 1451
       URR region is described in: "From average parameters to    4759 1451
       statistical resolved resonances", D. Rochman et al.,       4759 1451
       Annals of Nucl. Ene. 51 (2013) 60.                         4759 1451
       The s-wave average level spacing is 16.62 eV and           4759 1451
       the s-wave neutron strength is 6e-05 1e-4.                 4759 1451
                                                                  4759 1451
  MF32: Covariance file for resonance parameters                  4759 1451
        The compact format is used to represent the covariance    4759 1451
        information on the resonance parameters. Uncertainties    4759 1451
        come from compilations, EXFOR or existing libraries and   4759 1451
        correlations between parameters are obtained following    4759 1451
        the method presented in NIM/A 589 (2008) 85.              4759 1451
